    "All schemes used a delayed acceptance kernel in the move step, based on the k-nearest neighbours surrogate of Section 4.2, with k = 3.",
    "This gave a decrease in CPU time of around 30% over the corresponding schemes which used a standard (pseudo-marginal) MH kernel.",
    "Using the settings described above, 50 replicate runs of each scheme were performed, and the results summarised in Table 2 and Figure 3.",
    "We again compare the accuracy of each scheme by reporting bias and root mean square error (RMSE) of the estimators of the marginal posterior means and standard deviations of each log θ i.",
